                <section class="content-section collapsed" id="ai-updates">
                    <h2 class="section-header" data-default-state="collapsed" style="background-color: var(--procore-accent-stone);">
                        <!-- LEFT ALIGNMENT FIX: Use title-wrapper -->
                        <div class="title-wrapper">
                            <span class="icon-3d-section">üß†</span> AI Updates
                        </div>
                        <span class="icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </h2>
                    <div class="section-content" style="display: none; background-color: var(--procore-light-text);">
                        <div class="card-grid">
                            
                            <!-- NEW CARD: Gemini in Chrome is now live for Procore! -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="Gemini Chrome Live Procore Ctrl+G Alt+G Summarizing Explaining Quizzing Discussing">
                                <h3>Gemini in Chrome is now live for Procore!</h3>
                                <p>Gemini now lives right inside Chrome. It pops open in a small floating window so you can ask for help in the moment, using context from the tab you‚Äôre on, when you want it.</p>
                                
                                <p><b>How to start:</b> Open Chrome ‚Üí click the Gemini icon at the top right ‚Üí opt in once.</p>
                                
                                <p><b>Bonus:</b> After opt-in, you‚Äôll see Gemini in your Mac menu bar or Windows tray and can use keyboard shortcuts. (Mac: <b>Ctrl + G</b> | Windows: <b>Alt + G</b>)</p>

                                <p><b>Gemini in Chrome is good for:</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Summarizing a page you‚Äôre reading</li>
                                    <li>Explaining tricky topics in plain English</li>
                                    <li>Quizzing yourself on something new</li>
                                    <li>Discussing the information on your tab and going deeper on concepts</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="source-info">
                                    <i>Helpful Links: <a href="https://support.google.com/gemini/?p=get_started_chrome_extension" target="_blank">Getting Started with Gemini in Chrome</a> | <a href="https://support.google.com/gemini/answer/14569550" target="_blank">Use Gemini Live w/ Gemini in Chrome</a></i>
                                    </p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <!-- Existing Card 1: Presentations with Gemini -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="Presentations with Gemini create decks upload document Canvas Google Slides">
                                <h3>Presentations with Gemini</h3>
                                <p>You can now create entire presentations <b>inside</b> the Gemini app. Give Gemini a prompt, or upload a document (brief, your notes, a 20-page report), select "Canvas" from tools and it will generate a full deck, complete with a theme and images. Then, export it to Google Slides to add your final polish.</p>
                                <p class="source-info"><i>Before: Crying softly as you try to turn a 10-page doc into a Q4 kickoff deck.</i></p>
                                <p class="source-info"><i>Now: Upload the doc. Select Canvas. Ask Gemini to "create a launch presentation". Get a 10-slide head start in 60 seconds.</i></p>
                                <p class="source-info">
                                    <i>Source: <a href="https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2025/10/generate-presentations-in-gemini-app.html" target="_blank">Google Workspace Updates</a></i>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <!-- Existing Card 2: NotebookLM Upgrade -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="NotebookLM Upgrade Bigger Brain Custom Goals skeptical research advisor">
                                <h3>NotebookLM: Now with a Bigger Brain (and an 'Attitude')</h3>
                                <p>Your personal AI research assistant just got a serious engine upgrade. It now has an <b>8x larger context window</b> (1 million tokens!) and <b>6x longer conversation memory</b>. The best part? <b>Custom Goals</b>‚ÄîYou can now tell NotebookLM exactly how to act:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>"Act as a skeptical marketing director. Poke holes in this launch plan. Be direct and analytical."</li>
                                    <li>"You are my research advisor. Rigorously challenge every assumption I make".</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="source-info">
                                    <i>Source: <a href="https://blog.google/technology/google-labs/notebooklm-custom-personas-engine-upgrade/" target="_blank">Google Labs Blog</a></i>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <!-- Existing Card 3: Make Your Docs Look Crisp (LaTeX) -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="Make Your Docs Look Crisp LaTeX professional documents project proposals technical guides PDF">
                                <h3>Make Your Docs Look Crisp with LaTeX</h3>
                                <p>"LaTeX" is the secret code for making documents look incredibly professional <b>without</b> fighting a word processor. Gemini now makes you a LaTeX expert.</p>
                                <p class="source-info"><i>Before: Your project proposal looks messy in a standard doc.</i></p>
                                <p class="source-info"><i>Now: Ask Gemini to "Format this content as a clean, professional project proposal using LaTeX." It generates a perfect, sharp PDF you can download.</i></p>
                                <p class="source-info">
                                    <i>Source: <a href="https://workspaceupdates.googleblog.com/2025/10/new-latex-features-in-gemini-app.html" target="_blank">Google Workspace Updates</a></i>
                                </p>
