                <!-- 3. Legal Industry News Section -->
                <!-- ************************************ -->
                <section class="content-section collapsed" id="ai-news">
                    <h2 class="section-header" data-default-state="collapsed" style="background-color: var(--procore-accent-stone);">
                        <!-- LEFT ALIGNMENT FIX: Use title-wrapper -->
                        <div class="title-wrapper">
                            <span class="icon-3d-section">üì∞</span> Legal Industry News
                        </div>
                        <span class="icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                    </h2>
                    <div class="section-content" style="display: none; background-color: var(--procore-light-text);">
                        <div class="card-grid">
                            
                            <!-- CONSOLIDATED Article 1: ACC AI Toolkit Summary (SHORTER VERSION) -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="ACC AI Toolkit Governance IP Ethics Competence Confidentiality Policy Leadership Risk Management">
                                <h3>ACC AI Toolkit Summary: 3 Pillars of Legal AI Readiness</h3>
                                <p>The ACC's toolkit outlines the critical role in-house lawyers play in navigating the AI landscape, focusing on three key areas:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><b>AI Governance:</b> Lead cross-functional audits, map regulations (like the EU AI Act), and implement business-friendly policies that balance risks and rewards.</li>
                                    <li><b>Protecting IP & Ethics:</b> Satisfy the duty of competence (learn AI tools) and confidentiality (prevent data leaks). Use <b>secure, private platforms</b> and ensure human oversight.</li>
                                    <li><b>Career Readiness:</b> Use AI to shift focus from routine work to <b>high-value strategy</b>. AI literacy is now an ethical requirement.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="source-info">
                                    <!-- FIX: Ensure target="_blank" is used for external ACC link -->
                                    <span style="font-style: italic;">Source: <a href="https://www.acc.com/sites/default/files/resources/upload/ACC-Artificial-Intelligence-Toolkit-for-In-house-Lawyers-FINAL.pdf" target="_blank">ACC Artificial Intelligence Toolkit for In-house Lawyers</a></span>
                                </p>
                            </div>

                            <!-- NEW Article 2: Bloomberg Law Update -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="Bloomberg Law In-house Gen AI Use Doubles Legal Operations Productivity Efficiency">
                                <h3>In-House Use of Gen AI More Than Doubles in One Year</h3>
                                <p>A recent Bloomberg Law survey reveals a massive surge in generative AI adoption within corporate legal departments. Use of Gen AI tools like Gemini and CoPilot has <b class="orange-bold">more than doubled</b> in the last 12 months, driven primarily by the need for increased efficiency and productivity in routine tasks.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><b>Primary Driver:</b> Speed and productivity in drafting, research, and summarization.</li>
                                    <li><b>Key Users:</b> Adoption is highest among legal operations professionals and younger in-house counsel.</li>
                                    <li><b>Focus Shift:</b> The focus is moving beyond simple curiosity to implementing tools for <b class="orange-bold">core business workflows</b> that deliver measurable value.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="source-info">
                                    <i>Source: <a href="https://news.bloomberglaw.com/artificial-intelligence/in-house-lawyers-use-of-gen-al-more-than-doubles-in-one-year" target="_blank">Bloomberg Law</a></i>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <!-- NEW Article 3: Devil's Advocate Update -->
                            <div class="card" data-search-term="AI Devil's Advocate Sparring Partner Legal Strategy Weaknesses Opposing Counsel">
                                <h3>AI: The New Devil's Advocate for Legal Strategy</h3>
                                <p>This article highlights a sophisticated use case where generative AI acts as a <b class="orange-bold">sparring partner</b>, challenging a lawyer's core arguments and helping to anticipate opposing counsel's responses in complex disputes.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><b>Strategic Use:</b> Feeding core legal arguments into an AI model with a prompt like "Act as opposing counsel" can expose unseen weaknesses.</li>
                                    <li><b>Core Benefit:</b> It inverts the traditional workflow by <b class="orange-bold">automating information gathering</b> (the 80% time drain) and freeing lawyers to concentrate on <b class="orange-bold">high-value strategic analysis</b> (the 20% value-add).</li>
                                <li><b>Impact:</b> AI provides "superpowers" to a lawyer's strategic intuition, strengthening submissions and reducing vulnerability to surprise attacks.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="source-info">
                                <i>Source: <a href="https://www.lawyersweekly.com.au/corporate-counsel/43221-could-ai-be-the-new-devil-s-advocate-for-in-house-lawyers" target="_blank">Lawyers Weekly</a></i>
                                </p>
